derived from two independent subscriptions to the same cell (packages/app/src/client/App.tsx:760 (HostCard) vs :557/:582 (watchByEntry + badge))FILE .lens-debate/hickey-1.msg\nfix(lens): drop the unread pct field from the alert wire\n\npct was computed by the fold, validated by the schema, and shipped on every\nframe, but no consumer reads it — alertsEqual itself ignores it. Remove pct from\nAlertItem, AlertsSchema, and the fold's raised.set, and delete the pct-specific\ntest plus the pct fields from the remaining expectations. If a UI ever wants\n\"pct at raise,\" add it back when there is a reader.\n\nAgreed by the lowy ⇄ hickey lens debate (finding hickey-1, raised by hickey). Not pushed or merged.\nFILE .lens-debate/hickey-3.msg\nfix(lens): collapse the one-field AlertItem to a bare AlertId[]\n\nWith label and pct gone, AlertItem was {id} — a record wrapping a single field.\nThe concept is a set of raised ids, so make the shape say so: Alerts becomes\n{items: AlertId[]}, AlertsSchema an array of the id enum, applyHysteresis folds\nover a Set<AlertId> (add/delete, rebuild via METRIC_IDS.filter), alertsEqual is\nset-equality over the id arrays, and watchByEntry's selector collapses to\nidentity. Tests updated to the [\"cpu\"] shape.\n\nAgreed by the lowy ⇄ hickey lens debate (finding hickey-3, raised by hickey). Not pushed or merged.\nFILE .lens-debate/lowy-1.msg\nfix(lens): single-source the metric vocabulary and system→% projection\n\nAdd MetricKey + metricPercents to drishti-common/metrics as the one home for\n\"which metrics exist\" and \"how a system snapshot projects to per-metric\npercentages\"; alerts.ts now aliases AlertId=MetricKey and MetricsFrame=\nRecord<MetricKey,number> and drops the duplicated metricsFrameOf (agent and\ncaptureSample both call metricPercents), collapsing the parallel union and\nprojection into one.\n\nAgreed by the lowy ⇄ hickey lens debate (finding lowy-1, raised by lowy). Not pushed or merged.\nFILE .lens-debate/lowy-2.msg\nfix(lens): move the alert label off the wire into the client\n\nPresentation vocabulary was single-sourced in the agent's fold and shipped on\nevery AlertItem. Drop `label` from AlertItem, AlertsSchema, and the fold;\nrelocate the Title-Case LABELS map to the client (App.tsx) where rename/localize\nbelongs, rewrite the notification title as LABELS[id], and delete labelOf and\nits impossible `?? id` fallback. The wire now carries only {id, pct}; AlertId\nstays exported from drishti-common as a legitimate wire id.\n\nAgreed by the lowy ⇄ hickey lens debate (finding lowy-2, raised by lowy). Not pushed or merged.\nFILE .lens-debate/lowy-3.msg\nfix(lens): delete the hollow app/common/metrics re-export barrel\n\nAfter the pct helpers moved to drishti-common/metrics, this module was a pure\nredirect encapsulating no volatility — a backward-compat shim, which the design\nphilosophy calls a defect to remove. Delete it and repoint its last consumer\n(client/metrics.ts) directly at drishti-common/metrics; history.ts already\nresolves there. One home, no redirect.\n\nAgreed by the lowy ⇄ hickey lens debate (finding lowy-3, raised by lowy). Not pushed or merged.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
